<section class="section section--alt" id="kitchen-sink-f1-form-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Before you send it</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">The questions buyers actually ask.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list">
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="kitchen-sink-f1-form-faq-a1">What does the discovery call cost?</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="kitchen-sink-f1-form-faq-a1" data-open="false">
          <p>Nothing. The 30-minute discovery call is complimentary, there&rsquo;s no hourly billing, and the written fixed-fee scope that follows is non-binding. Every engagement is priced from the canonical figures published on our <a href="/pricing/">pricing page</a> &mdash; the scope you receive cites them.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="kitchen-sink-f1-form-faq-a2">Will I get a sales pitch on the call?</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="kitchen-sink-f1-form-faq-a2" data-open="false">
          <p>No. A Certified ProAdvisor reviews where your books are and recommends the right engagement &mdash; or none, if that&rsquo;s the honest answer. There&rsquo;s no commission for steering you anywhere, no follow-up sales sequence, and the call ends with a clear next step you&rsquo;re free to ignore.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="kitchen-sink-f1-form-faq-a3">What if TechBrot isn&rsquo;t the right fit for my situation?</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="kitchen-sink-f1-form-faq-a3" data-open="false">
          <p>We&rsquo;ll say so on the call and point you toward what does fit &mdash; including firms outside TechBrot when that&rsquo;s the honest answer. The discovery call is complimentary either way, and you keep everything you learned from it.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="kitchen-sink-f1-form-faq-a4">Do you only work with businesses already on QuickBooks?</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="kitchen-sink-f1-form-faq-a4" data-open="false">
          <p>No. If you&rsquo;re on Xero, Wave, other software, or spreadsheets, the discovery call covers whether a <a href="/quickbooks/migration/">migration</a> or a fresh <a href="/quickbooks/setup/">QuickBooks setup</a> makes sense &mdash; and if staying put is the right answer, we&rsquo;ll tell you that. New businesses with no accounting infrastructure yet are a regular starting point.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="kitchen-sink-f1-form-faq-a5">How does pricing work after the discovery call?</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="kitchen-sink-f1-form-faq-a5" data-open="false">
          <p>You get a written fixed-fee scope within 3 business days of the call. It binds us to the fee and the deliverables; it doesn&rsquo;t bind you. If genuinely new in-scope work emerges mid-engagement, we re-quote in writing before any of it happens &mdash; no scope creep, no hourly upcharges. Canonical figures live on the <a href="/pricing/">pricing page</a>.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="kitchen-sink-f1-form-faq-a6">Will I end up on a marketing list if I submit the form?</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="kitchen-sink-f1-form-faq-a6" data-open="false">
          <p>No. Your details are used only to respond to this request &mdash; no marketing list, no sales follow-up sequence. The <a href="/legal/privacy-policy/">privacy policy</a> covers exactly what happens to the information in the brief.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="kitchen-sink-f1-form-faq-a7">My situation is urgent — can I skip the form?</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="kitchen-sink-f1-form-faq-a7" data-open="false">
          <p>Yes. Call <a href="tel:+18777515575" data-tb-event="phone_click">(877) 751-5575</a>, Mon&ndash;Fri 9&nbsp;AM&ndash;6&nbsp;PM ET &mdash; a ProAdvisor answers during business hours. Or book directly on <a href="https://calendly.com/techbrot/discovery" rel="noopener">our calendar</a> without filling the form. Same operator, same outcome; the form just gets us the details before the call.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="kitchen-sink-f1-form-faq-a8">We&rsquo;re a multi-entity or multi-year situation — does the free review still apply?</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="kitchen-sink-f1-form-faq-a8" data-open="false">
          <p>The diagnostic-level read is still free for one entity. Multi-entity or multi-year files genuinely take longer to assess accurately, and may need a paid deep diagnostic before a fixed-fee scope is honest &mdash; typically a flat fee credited toward the engagement if you proceed. We&rsquo;ll tell you <em>before</em> the meter starts, on the discovery call, and you can stop there at no cost.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="kitchen-sink-f1-form-faq-a9">Who actually reviews the file?</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="kitchen-sink-f1-form-faq-a9" data-open="false">
          <p>A Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor &mdash; typically our lead practice for the diagnostic itself. If the engagement after the review is best matched to a vetted local operator like Westgate Financial Services in Texas, we&rsquo;ll introduce you. The Certified ProAdvisor doing the review is the same person you talk to on the diagnostic call &mdash; never a rotating queue, never a junior offshore.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
